ach, followed by 20 minutes of debate with the attendants.\r\n\r\n	Fishbowls and Open Spaces will also have their place on the schedule, but they will be proposed in an ad-hoc fashion by the conference attendants, during the conference.\r\n\r\n	As always, we encourage everyone to <a href=\"http://submissoes.agilebrazil.com/\">submit your proposals</a>. Presenting at Agile Brazil is a way of enriching Agile\'s state-of-art in Brazil and of receiving feedback from the community. Plan your submission and make part of it!\r\n\r\n	Program committee\r\n	<strong>Agile Brazil 2014</strong>\r\n</article>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Schedule','','publish','open','open','','program','','','2014-06-21 21:35:30','2014-06-21 21:35:30','',0,'http://2014.staging.agilebrazil.com/?page_id=280',0,'page','',0),(281,1,'2014-05-09 22:10:56','2014-05-09 22:10:56','TBD','Schedule','','inherit','open','open','','280-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 22:10:56','2014-05-09 22:10:56','',280,'http://2014.staging.agilebrazil.com/uncategorized/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2014-05-09 22:31:42','2014-05-09 22:31:42','This is the call for papers of Agile Brazil 2014! In 2014, Brazil\'s biggest conference on agile methods will take place at the wonderful city of Florianópolis from 5th to 7th november.\n\nThe conference organization is working in order to provide yet another high value event to the agile community, with presentations and discussions in various topics and optics. On that matter, we hope that you participate with your stories, ideas and activities!\n\nOn april, we will be ready to receive your submission through the already known Agile Brazil\'s submission system. Until then, start thinking on what you and your friends will be presenting this year.\n\nThe tracks for this year are:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>General Interest</li>\n	<li>Development and Tests</li>\n	<li>Management</li>\n	<li>Coaching, Teaching and Facilitation</li>\n	<li>UX, Product Analysis and Design</li>